00:08:02,273 --> 00:08:04,232
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}what do you say we go find Dr. Cawley?

81
00:08:16,287 --> 00:08:18,955
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}When did she escape? This prisoner?

82
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:23,210
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm afraid Dr. Cawley will have to fill you in on the situation. Protocol.

83
00:08:23,294 --> 00:08:25,420
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Correctional officers at a mental institution,

84
00:08:25,505 --> 00:08:27,672
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}that's a weird sight, if you don't mind me saying.

85
00:08:27,757 --> 00:08:31,176
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}McPHERSON: It's the only facility of its kind in the U.S., even the world.

86
00:08:31,260 --> 00:08:33,803
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We take only the most dangerous, damaged patients,

87
00:08:33,888 --> 00:08:35,847
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}ones no other hospital can manage.

88
00:08:35,932 --> 00:08:37,849
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And it's all due to Dr. Cawley.

89
00:08:37,934 --> 00:08:39,851
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's created something really unique here.

90
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:43,522
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's a hospital for people our society normally considers beyond treatment.

91
00:09:08,130 --> 00:09:10,090
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Top of his class at Johns Hopkins, then Harvard...

